HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 299
BY REPRESENTATIVE LACOMBE
A RESOLUTION
To commemorate the fortieth anniversary of Entergy's River Bend Station and to recognize
the important role nuclear power plays in providing safe and reliable electricity to
Louisiana.
WHEREAS, Entergy's River Bend Station has proudly served the residents of West
Feliciana Parish, the state of Louisiana, and the Gulf Coast region for forty years and
provided safe, reliable, and carbon-free electricity since commencing commercial operation
in 1986; and
WHEREAS, River Bend Station is a cornerstone of energy resilience in Southeast
Louisiana, and it plays a vital role in meeting the power needs of nearly half a million
customers by providing a maximum dependable capacity of nine hundred seventy-eight
megawatts, and contributing to grid stability during periods of peak demand and extreme
weather events; and
WHEREAS, River Bend Station has more than eight hundred employees and
contractors who have demonstrated a commitment to operational excellence, nuclear safety,
emergency preparedness, and professional standards; these persons exemplify the spirit of
public service and technical leadership; and
WHEREAS, River Bend Station maintains a strong and ongoing partnership with the
West Feliciana, East Feliciana, Pointe Coupee, and East Baton Rouge communities by
providing local jobs, supporting charitable organizations, investing in STEM education, and
preparing future generations through workforce development initiatives; and
